{"title":"OpenBSD","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/OpenBSD","type":"markdown","data":"[![Wikipedia](/images/thumb/f/f8/Fair-use-wikipedia-logo.png/50px-Fair-use-wikipedia-logo.png)](/wiki/File:Fair-use-wikipedia-logo.png \"Wikipedia\")\n\n[Wikipedia](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_Page \"wikipedia:Main Page\") has an article about:\n\n***[OpenBSD](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:Search/OpenBSD \"wikipedia:Special:Search/OpenBSD\")***\n\nSeen at the end of the package description for [NetHack](/wiki/NetHack \"NetHack\") on **OpenBSD**:\n\n*\"P.S. This is a very addictive game, with its whole wacky culture. And even a newsgroup dedicated to it ([rec.games.roguelike.nethack](/wiki/Rec.games.roguelike.nethack \"Rec.games.roguelike.nethack\")). Don't say we didn't warn you !\"*\n\n***\n\n**OpenBSD** is a variant of [BSD](/wiki/BSD \"BSD\"), one form of [Unix](/wiki/Unix \"Unix\"). The [OpenBSD Packages Collection](http://www.openbsd.org/faq/faq15.html) includes copies of [NetHack](/wiki/NetHack \"NetHack\"), [Falcon's Eye](/wiki/Falcon%27s_Eye \"Falcon's Eye\"), [SLASH](/wiki/SLASH \"SLASH\") and [SLASH'EM](/wiki/SLASH%27EM \"SLASH'EM\").\n\nFor OpenBSD 3.9, there are packages of Falcon's Eye 1.9.3, NetHack 3.4.3, SLASH E8 and SLASH'EM 0.0.7E7F1. The easiest way to install them is to go to the [package lists](http://www.openbsd.org/3.9_packages/), choose your architecture, look for packages called \"nethack\", \"falconseye\", \"slash\", and \"slash-em\", then give their FTP urls to the `pkg_add` command.\n\nNote that the latest version of SLASH'EM is 0.0.7E7F2.\n\n***\n\nYou might not want to use the packages on **OpenBSD**. You can just [telnet](/wiki/Telnet \"Telnet\") to a [public server](/wiki/Public_server \"Public server\") and play. Locally (if the system has the install set `games-XX.tgz` installed) you can play [Hack 1.0.3](/wiki/Hack_1.0.3 \"Hack 1.0.3\") by typing `hack` at the command line.\n\nIf you want to use some [patches](/wiki/Patch \"Patch\"), then you will need to build the game yourself. In this case, you might consult `/usr/ports/games/nethack/patches` for hints on how to configure the sources.\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>OpenBSD - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"OpenBSD\",\"wgTitle\":\"OpenBSD\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":131584,\"wgRevisionId\":131584,\"wgArticleId\":5047,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Operating systems\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"OpenBSD\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":5047,\"wgRequestId\":\"e8d3c262abd71b3488708620\",\"wgCSPNonce\":false,\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRestrictionEdit\":[],\"wgRestrictionMove\":[],\"wgWikiEditorEnabledModules\":[],\"wgCategoryTreePageCategoryOptions\":\"{\\\"mode\\\":0,\\\"hideprefix\\\":20,\\\"showcount\\\":true,\\\"namespaces\\\":false}\"});mw.loader.state({\"site.styles\":\"ready\",\"noscript\":\"ready\",\"user.styles\":\"ready\",\"user\":\"ready\",\"user.options\":\"ready\",\"user.tokens\":\"loading\",\"mediawiki.legacy.shared\":\"ready\",\"mediawiki.legacy.commonPrint\":\"ready\",\"mediawiki.skinning.interface\":\"ready\",\"skins.vector.styles\":\"ready\"});mw.loader.implement(\"user.tokens@0tffind\",function($,jQuery,require,module){/*@nomin*/mw.user.tokens.set({\"editToken\":\"+\\\\\",\"patrolToken\":\"+\\\\\",\"watchToken\":\"+\\\\\",\"csrfToken\":\"+\\\\\"});\n});RLPAGEMODULES=[\"site\",\"mediawiki.page.startup\",\"mediawiki.user\",\"mediawiki.page.ready\",\"mediawiki.searchSuggest\",\"skins.vector.js\"];mw.loader.load(RLPAGEMODULES);});</script>\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=mediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmediawiki.skinning.interface%7Cskins.vector.styles&amp;only=styles&amp;skin=vector\"/>\n<script async=\"\" src=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=startup&amp;only=scripts&amp;skin=vector\"></script>\n<meta name=\"ResourceLoaderDynamicStyles\" content=\"\"/>\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=site.styles&amp;only=styles&amp;skin=vector\"/>\n<meta name=\"generator\" content=\"MediaWiki 1.32.5\"/>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"Seen at the end of the package description for NetHack on OpenBSD:\"/>\n<link rel=\"image_src\" href=\"/images/6/65/Nethackwiki-logo.png\"/>\n<link rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"/images/6/64/Favicon.ico\"/>\n<link rel=\"search\" type=\"application/opensearchdescription+xml\" href=\"/opensearch_desc.php\" title=\"NetHackWiki\"/>\n<link rel=\"EditURI\" type=\"application/rsd+xml\" href=\"https://nethackwiki.com/api.php?action=rsd\"/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"/wiki/OpenBSD\"/>\n<!--[if lt IE 9]><script src=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=html5shiv&amp;only=scripts&amp;skin=vector&amp;sync=1\"></script><![endif]-->\n</head>\n<body class=\"mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr mw-hide-empty-elt ns-0 ns-subject page-OpenBSD rootpage-OpenBSD skin-vector action-view\">\t\t<div id=\"mw-page-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"mw-head-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"content\" class=\"mw-body\" role=\"main\">\n\t\t\t<a id=\"top\"></a>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"mw-indicators mw-body-content\">\n</div>\n<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">OpenBSD</h1>\t\t\t<div id=\"bodyContent\" class=\"mw-body-content\">\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"siteSub\" class=\"noprint\">From NetHackWiki</div>\t\t\t\t<div id=\"contentSub\"></div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"jump-to-nav\"></div>\t\t\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#mw-head\">Jump to navigation</a>\n\t\t\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#p-search\">Jump to search</a>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\" class=\"mw-content-ltr\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"noprint sidebox\">\n<div style=\"float: left;\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Fair-use-wikipedia-logo.png\" class=\"image\" title=\"Wikipedia\"><img alt=\"Wikipedia\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f8/Fair-use-wikipedia-logo.png/50px-Fair-use-wikipedia-logo.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/f/f8/Fair-use-wikipedia-logo.png 1.5x\" /></a></div></div>\n<div style=\"margin-left: 60px;\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_Page\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wikipedia:Main Page\">Wikipedia</a> has an article about:\n<div style=\"margin-left: 10px;\"><i><b><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:Search/OpenBSD\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wikipedia:Special:Search/OpenBSD\">OpenBSD </a></b></i></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>Seen at the end of the package description for <a href=\"/wiki/NetHack\" title=\"NetHack\">NetHack</a> on <b>OpenBSD</b>:\n</p><p><i>\"P.S. This is a very addictive game, with its whole wacky culture. And even a newsgroup dedicated to it (<a href=\"/wiki/Rec.games.roguelike.nethack\" title=\"Rec.games.roguelike.nethack\">rec.games.roguelike.nethack</a>). Don't say we didn't warn you&#160;!\"</i>\n</p>\n<hr />\n<p><b>OpenBSD</b> is a variant of <a href=\"/wiki/BSD\" title=\"BSD\">BSD</a>, one form of <a href=\"/wiki/Unix\" title=\"Unix\">Unix</a>. The <a class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.openbsd.org/faq/faq15.html\">OpenBSD Packages Collection</a> includes copies of <a href=\"/wiki/NetHack\" title=\"NetHack\">NetHack</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Falcon%27s_Eye\" title=\"Falcon&#39;s Eye\">Falcon's Eye</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/SLASH\" title=\"SLASH\">SLASH</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/SLASH%27EM\" title=\"SLASH&#39;EM\">SLASH'EM</a>.\n</p><p>For OpenBSD 3.9, there are packages of Falcon's Eye 1.9.3, NetHack 3.4.3, SLASH E8 and SLASH'EM 0.0.7E7F1. The easiest way to install them is to go to the <a class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.openbsd.org/3.9_packages/\">package lists</a>, choose your architecture, look for packages called \"nethack\", \"falconseye\", \"slash\", and \"slash-em\", then give their FTP urls to the <tt>pkg_add</tt> command.\n</p><p>Note that the latest version of SLASH'EM is 0.0.7E7F2.\n</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You might not want to use the packages on <b>OpenBSD</b>. You can just <a href=\"/wiki/Telnet\" title=\"Telnet\">telnet</a> to a <a href=\"/wiki/Public_server\" title=\"Public server\">public server</a> and play. Locally (if the system has the install set <tt>games-XX.tgz</tt> installed) you can play <a href=\"/wiki/Hack_1.0.3\" title=\"Hack 1.0.3\">Hack 1.0.3</a> by typing <tt>hack</tt> at the command line.\n</p><p>If you want to use some <a href=\"/wiki/Patch\" title=\"Patch\">patches</a>, then you will need to build the game yourself. In this case, you might consult <tt>/usr/ports/games/nethack/patches</tt> for hints on how to configure the sources.\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240926185514\nCache expiry: 604800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.008 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.024 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 25/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 100/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 646/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 137/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 4/40\nExpensive parser function co